# Round 07's HomeGenerator embed is now obsolete

Round 07 added an inline `<HomeGenerator />` section between Hero and Content
on the homepage. With Round 09, the homepage is a marketing-focused funnel
that sends visitors to /best-ai-art-generator instead of embedding the
generator directly.

If Round 07 was previously applied, Round 09's `app/routes/home.tsx`
replacement already drops the `<HomeGenerator />` import and render. No
manual diff needed — the route file replacement handles it.

The component file itself can stay at:

  app/components/homepage/HomeGenerator.tsx

It's no longer referenced. Delete or keep — either is fine. (Keeping leaves
the option open to re-embed later if data shows visitors want to try without
clicking through to /best-ai-art-generator.)

If you want to delete it cleanly:

    rm app/components/homepage/HomeGenerator.tsx

That's the only "diff" — Round 09 is a full route replacement, so all the
import and render changes are baked in.
